The arms, recorded some thirty years earlier in the Lyon Register, are: “Gules a chevron argent betwixt three skens of the second hefted and pomelld or, surmounted of als many woolfs heads couped of the third tusked proper.” Crest: “A dexter hand issuing out of ane cloud reaching a garland of Lawrell fructuated.” Motto: “Gratis a Deo data”
